
<h2><span class="badge bg-warning"><i class="fab fa-leanpub"></i> Yeshua in the Tanakh</span></h2>

<p class="text-muted"><small><i>Tanakh</i> is the Old Testament</small></p>

<p class="h5">
	<b>Luke 24:13-34</b> tells the story of two disciples who were walking on the road to Emmaus, talking with each other about the recent death of Yeshua.
	They were joined on their journey by the resurrected Messiah.
</p>

@*
	THIS DOESN'T WORK, EVEN THOUGH I HAVE NO ISSUES AT https://localhost:5001/Leadership (see the quote from Psalms 19:1)
	THE DIFFERENCE IS THAT HERE IT IS WRAPPED iNSIDE <ContentTemplate></ContentTemplate>
	SOLUTION: Wrap the <i> and <blockquote> inside a <div>
*@

<p>
	<BibleQuote Cite="Luke 24:27">
		<p class="fs-5 text-primary">
			Then beginning with Moses and with all the prophets, He explained to them the things concerning Himself in all the Scriptures.
		</p>
	</BibleQuote>
</p>

<p class="lead">
	Listed below are some of the Scriptures in the Tanakh (Old Testament) that Yeshua probably used when speaking with these two men on the road to Emmaus.
</p>

<div class="row">
	<div class="col-sm-3">

		<button type="button" class="btn btn-info btn-sm" @onclick="@(e => ToggleVersePopupClick(IsCollapsed, 1))">
			Genesis 49:10
		</button>
		<blockquote class="blockquote">
			<sup>10</sup> The scepter shall not depart from Judah,<br />
			Nor the ruler’s staff from between his feet,<br />
			Until Shiloh comes*,<br />
			And to him shall be the obedience of the peoples.<br /><br />
			* Or <i>Until he comes to Shiloh</i>; or <i>Until he comes to whom it belongs</i><br /><br />
			<small><b>Genesis 49:10</b></small>
		</blockquote>

	</div>

	<div class="col-sm-3">
		<button type="button" class="btn btn-info btn-sm" @onclick="@(e => ToggleVersePopupClick(IsCollapsed, 2))">
			Deuteronomy 18:15
		</button>
		<blockquote class="blockquote">
			<sup>15</sup> The LORD your God will raise up for you a prophet like me from among you, from your countrymen, you shall listen to him.
			<small><b>Deuteronomy 18:15</b></small>
		</blockquote>
	</div>

	<div class="col-sm-3">
		<div class="card card-body bg-light">

			<button type="button" class="btn btn-info btn-sm" @onclick="@(e => ToggleVersePopupClick(IsCollapsed, 3))">
				Isaiah 7:14
			</button>
			<blockquote class="blockquote">
				<sup>14</sup> Therefore the Lord Himself will give you a sign: Behold, a virgin will be with child and bear a son, and she will call His name Immanuel.
				<small><b>Isaiah 7:14</b></small>
			</blockquote>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="col-sm-3">
		<button type="button" class="btn btn-info btn-sm" @onclick="@(e => ToggleVersePopupClick(IsCollapsed, 4))">
			Isaiah 9:6-7
		</button>
		<blockquote class="blockquote">
			<sup>6</sup> For a child will be born to us, a son will be given to us;
			And the government will rest on His shoulders;
			And His name will be called Wonderful Counselor, Mighty God,
			Eternal Father, Prince of Peace.<br />
			<sup>7</sup> There will be no end to the increase of His government or of peace,
			On the throne of David and over his kingdom,
			To establish it and to uphold it with justice and righteousness
			From then on and forevermore.
			The zeal of the Lord of hosts will accomplish this.
			<small><b>Isaiah 9:6-7</b></small>
		</blockquote>
	</div>
</div>

@* <div class="row col-12">
	<p class="text-muted">ToDo: this modal function is not working yet</p>
</div>
 *@

@code {
	public bool IsCollapsed { get; set; } = true;
	public int VerseId { get; set; }
	public string ButtonText { get; set; } = "Details";
	public string ButtonChevron { get; set; } = " fas fa-chevron-down";
	protected void ToggleVersePopupClick(bool isCollapsed, int verseId)
	{
		IsCollapsed = !isCollapsed;
		VerseId = verseId;
		ButtonText = IsCollapsed ? "Details" : "Hide";
		ButtonChevron = IsCollapsed ? "fas fa-chevron-down" : "fas fa-chevron-up";
	}
}
